ular expression method throws a <xref:System.Text.RegularExpressions.RegexMatchTimeoutException> exception."},{"content":"In your exception handler, you can choose to retry the match with a longer time-out interval, abandon the match attempt and assume that there is no match, or abandon the match attempt and log the exception information for future analysis.","pos":[31127,31365]},{"content":"The following example defines a <ph id=\"ph1\">`GetWordData`</ph> method that instantiates a regular expression with a time-out interval of 350 milliseconds to calculate the number of words and average number of characters in a word in a text document.","pos":[31372,31604],"source":"The following example defines a `GetWordData` method that instantiates a regular expression with a time-out interval of 350 milliseconds to calculate the number of words and average number of characters in a word in a text document."},{"content":"If the matching operation times out, the time-out interval is increased by 350 milliseconds and the <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Text.RegularExpressions.Regex&gt;</ph> object is re-instantiated.","pos":[31605,31775],"source":" If the matching operation times out, the time-out interval is increased by 350 milliseconds and the <xref:System.Text.RegularExpressions.Regex> object is re-instantiated."},{"content":"If the new time-out interval exceeds 1 second, the method re-throws the exception to the caller.","pos":[31776,31872]},{"pos":[31879,32230],"content":"[!code-csharp[Conceptual.RegularExpressions.BestPractices#12](../../../samples/snippets/csharp/VS_Snippets_CLR/conceptual.regularexpressions.bestpractices/cs/timeout1.cs#12)]\n[!code-vb[Conceptual.RegularExpressions.BestPractices#12](../../../samples/snippets/visualbasic/VS_Snippets_CLR/conceptual.regularexpressions.bestpractices/vb/timeout1.vb#12)]","leadings":[""," "],"nodes":[{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">[!code-csharp</bpt><bpt id=\"p2\">[</bpt>Conceptual.RegularExpressions.BestPractices#12<ept id=\"p2\